 The presidential candidate of All Progressives Congress (APC) Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu has joined the list of prominent Nigerians congratulating songstress Tems for winning the Grammys. Asiwaju dropped a congratulatory post for the songstress to celebrate Tems’ achievement via his Twitter handle on Monday. READ ALSO: President Buhari Congratulates Tems Over Grammy Win At the 65th edition of the Grammy Awards last night at the Staples Center in Los Angeles, US, the 27-year-old singer received a Grammy in the ‘Best Melodic Rap Performance’ category for her feature on Future’s ‘Wait For U’ ft. Drake. The historic award sets her apart from other female Nigerian Afrobeats artistes as she became the first to bag the highly coveted music honour. Hailing Tems, the APC Presidential Candidate said: “I join other Nigerians in congratulating Temilade Openiyi aka Tems @temsbaby on winning the Grammy award in the Best Melodic Rap Performance category for her contribution to the hit song “Wait for U” – featuring Future and Drake.”